# Vertical Scalling Practical :

1. Launch an EC2 instance

2. SSH of the same instance

3. Install nginx in that instance
a. start instance 
b. enable nginx
c. go to html directory
d. create index.html [add text like "First Instance"]

4. To check servers Load 
a. -- click on instance id
b. scroll down and click on "Monitoring"

5. Increse the capacity of Instance
a. stop instance
b. select instance
c. -- click on actions
d. -- select change instance type
e. now you can change the instance type [after changing you can also see the charges of that type]

6. EBS Protection while luanching a Server
a. while you launch an server scroll down to bottom
b. --click on "Advanced" beside "Configure Storage"
c. -- click on "Delete on Termination" and select "No"

